⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Lavinia
node U1 · U1 · ⟦Lavinia:U1:63cca6⟧

WHO   — Lavinia — the silent wife given a voice
WHAT  — The narrator and protagonist of Lavinia — the silent woman of the Aeneid retold from within, who meets the dying poet Virgil in a sacred grove and learns she is both a real woman and a character he barely wrote.
WHERE — U1 · Le Guin  Framework inputs: standalone (after Virgil's Aeneid)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because the women of the old poems were given no words, and a voice withheld is a life half-lived; because to be written is not to be owned — even a fictional woman can claim her own story and her own peace.
HOW   — By telling her own tale at last — by tending the sacred fire of her people, refusing the suitor Turnus, marrying the stranger Aeneas, and living on past the poem's end as no epic ever let a wife do.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  The poet gave me no words, so I have taken them — I am not finished where his song ends; I am only beginning to be spoken.

spoken token : rur-son-pheik   ·   hex : 63cca6
